HEADWORD: Glaucous
<hw>Glau"cous</hw> <pr>(gl⟦add⟧"k⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>glaucus</ets>, Gr. <grk>glayko`s</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
a sea-green color; of a dull green passing into grayish blue.</def>
<rj><au>Lindley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Covered with a fine bloom or fine
white powder easily rubbed off, as that on a blue plum, or on a cabbage
leaf.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glaucus</ent>⟦br⟧
